"v.赎罪，补偿 【英】 v.赎罪，补偿(to make amends or reparation for; atone for) 【考】 expiate : guilt / correct : error(赎罪消除罪行/改错 消除错误) 【记】 ex+pi(=pious虔诚)+a te→显出虔诚→赎罪 【同】 同根词：piety(虔诚) ; impious(不虔诚的) 【例】 He tried to expiate his crimes by giving money to the church. v. 赎罪; 补偿; 纠正 【例】He tried to expiate his crimes by giving money 他以捐款来赎罪. 【记】ex出, pi = pious(adj 虔诚的)－显出虔诚的态度－赎罪ex出, pi, ate吃: 为了赎罪把pi吃掉! 【参】piety(n 虔诚); impious(adj 不虔诚的) 【类】expiate: guilt = correct: error 赎罪消除罪行 = 改错消除错误guilt: expiation = fatigue: repose 有罪行需要赎罪 = 疲劳需要休息 【记】源自pity 遗憾，抱歉，后悔，pious 虔诚的，尽责的；ex + pity 出于后悔，遗憾，抱歉来赔偿；ex + piate 音：赔呀，赔偿，补偿 【相关】pity 遗憾，抱歉，后悔，怜悯,同情，piety 虔诚，pious 虔诚的，尽责的， impious 不尊敬的,无信仰的, 不虔诚的 expiate (v.)  c.1600 (OED entry has a typographical error in the earliest date), from Latin expiatus, past participle of expiare ""to make amends, atone for"" (see expiation). Related: Expiable (1560s); expiated; expiating."
